4 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 57 O.S. 2021, Section 332.1A, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 332.1A. A. Each member and each alternate member of
7 the Pardon and Parole Board shall receive at least twelve (12) hours
8 of training for the first year and six (6) hours of training per
9 year thereafter on matters relating to the duties of the Board. The
10 training shall be provided by personnel of the Pardon and Parole
11 Board.
12 B. Each member and each alternate member of the Pardon and
13 Parole Board shall complete annual training based on guidance from
14 organizations that provide training and technical assistance related
15 to the probation and parole process. Annual training curriculum
16 shall include, but not be limited to, identifying, understanding and
17 targeting criminogenic needs, the principles of effective
18 intervention, core correctional practices and how to support and
19 encourage offender behavior change.
